                                <a href="#" class="accordion-title eheme-accordion-section font-bold accordionBtn">Do I need to fast?</a>
                                <div class="accordion-content" data-tab-content >
                                    <p>Only if you are over 50 years old and scheduled for a vascular screening. If so, please refrain from eating, drinking, or smoking for at least four hours prior to your appointment. Water is permissible, and you should continue to take any prescribed medications. Diabetic patients should check their to make sure it’s permissible to take their pills on an empty stomach.</p> 
                                </div>
                            </li>
                            <li class="accordion-item" data-accordion-item>
                                <a href="#" class="accordion-title eheme-accordion-section font-bold accordionBtn">What should I wear to my visit?</a>
                                <div class="accordion-content" data-tab-content>
                                    <p>Dress as you normally would. You will be given a pair of scrubs to change into upon arrival for your exam. If you are scheduled for a cardiac stress test, it is recommended that you bring athletic shoes. Women are advised to wear or bring a support bra, as underwire bras and take tops are not suitable for the cardiac stress test.</p>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                            <li class="accordion-item" data-accordion-item>
                                <a href="#" class="accordion-title eheme-accordion-section font-bold accordionBtn">How should I prepare for a mammogram?</a>
                                <div class="accordion-content" data-tab-content>
                                    <p>If your last mammogram was not taken at EHE, please bring your most recent film with you. This enables the radiologist to make a comparison study against your current films to identify any subtle changes. Do not apply cream, lotion, talcum powder, or deodorant on your upper body the day of your mammogram.</p>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                            <li class="accordion-item" data-accordion-item>
                                <a href="#" class="accordion-title eheme-accordion-section font-bold accordionBtn">Are any of the procedures optional?</a>
